kill_test.c takes one command-line argument flag, and creates 2 child processes, then sets one of child process flag value 1, and kills it.
gcc kill_test.c
./a.out 1 
./a.out 0
 

fork_test.c takes one command-line argument flag, and sets the main flag of process according to given value, and tries to fork it.  
gcc fork_test.c
./a.out 1 
./a.out 0
